and it makes me feel bad about myself.

16:51.260 --> 16:53.700
And that is why I cheated.

16:54.900 --> 16:57.140
That's the dumbest thing
I've ever heard!

16:58.460 --> 17:00.380
Just like that.

17:00.460 --> 17:04.980
And then I thought about it,
and I realized that I'm not sorry either!

17:06.180 --> 17:09.060
Hey!

17:10.180 --> 17:12.099
Michael,
what are you saying?

17:12.180 --> 17:17.260
I'm sayin' that we're not right for
each other, because you make me feel bad!

17:20.260 --> 17:22.780
And...

17:22.859 --> 17:24.700
And...

17:24.780 --> 17:26.900
I don't think I can
be with you anymore.

17:28.980 --> 17:31.020
I want to break up.

17:32.820 --> 17:35.980
Wait, break up?

17:36.060 --> 17:38.700
No, no. Michael, I was wrong.
Please, let's talk about this.

17:38.780 --> 17:41.020
- No.
- Wait, but Michael!

17:47.780 --> 17:49.660
Casey, we need to talk.

17:49.700 --> 17:53.220
Well, I'm a little swamped
right now, Foreplay.

17:55.580 --> 17:59.100
I think Donna thinks
you love her...

17:59.180 --> 18:01.260
and if you don't,
you shouldn't act like you do.

18:01.340 --> 18:03.700
What are you?
The love police?

18:03.740 --> 18:06.180
Hands up!
Love police is here.

18:06.260 --> 18:10.260
Hey, all I'm saying is that
if you don't love her...

18:10.340 --> 18:12.300
just don't be with her, okay?

18:12.380 --> 18:14.820
Because she's
a really special person...

18:14.900 --> 18:17.660
and someone out there
could really love her.

18:17.700 --> 18:19.980
Someone out there
or someone right here?

18:23.260 --> 18:25.340
Oh, hey, Eric.
What are you doing here?

18:25.420 --> 18:27.260
